Overview

[Ezr 8:1](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#001.md), The companions of Ezra, who
returned from Babylon; [Ezr 8:15](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#015.md), He
sends to Iddo for ministers for the temple; [Ezr
8:21](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#021.md), He keeps a fast; [Ezr
8:24](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#024.md), He commits the treasures to the
custody of the priests; [Ezr 8:31](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#031.md),
From Ahava they come to Jerusalem; [Ezr
8:33](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#033.md), The treasure is weighed in the
temple; [Ezr 8:36](../../../bib/kjv/ezr008.htm#036.md), The commission is
delivered.

